  "prompt": "Do employees at Spark Energy have a good work-life balance? Does this differ across positions and departments?",
  "response": "Employee experiences regarding work-life balance at Spark Energy can vary based on factors such as position, department, and individual circumstances. Generally, perceptions of work-life balance are influenced by company culture, management practices, workload, and job responsibilities.\n\nWhile some employees may feel they have a good work-life balance, others, particularly in more demanding roles or departments that operate under high pressure, might experience challenges. It's common for customer service or sales teams to face higher workloads, which can impact work-life balance compared to other roles.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date insights, it's recommended to consult employee reviews on platforms like Glassdoor or Indeed, where current and former employees share their experiences. Networking with current employees can also provide a clearer picture of how work-life balance may differ among various positions and departments within Spark Energy.",
